|\frac{x+y}{2}-\sqrt{xy}|+|\frac{x+y}{2}+\sqrt{xy}|=|x|+|y|
\left|\frac{x+y}{2}-\sqrt{xy}\right|= \left|\frac{x+y -2\sqrt{xy}}{2}\right| = \frac{(\sqrt{x}-\sqrt{y})^2}{2}
\left|\frac{x+y}{2}+\sqrt{xy}\right| = \left|\frac{ (\sqrt{x}+\sqrt{y})^2}{2}\right|
\frac{x+y}{2} \ge \sqrt{xy}
x,y > 0
\frac{x+y}{2} \le -\sqrt{xy}
x,y < 0.
t=0
t=1
|(-1)^t(a^2+b^2)-2ab|+|(-1)^t(a^2+b^2)+2ab|=2a^2+2b^2.
|a^2+b^2+(-1)^{t+1}2ab|+|a^2+b^2+(-1)^t2ab|=2a^2+2b^2.
|a^2+b^2-2ab|=|(a-b)^2|=(a-b)^2=a^2+b^2-2ab,
|a^2+b^2+2ab|=|(a+b)^2|=(a+b)^2=a^2+b^2+2ab.
